  <notes>
    Completed 2026-05-19. All acceptance criteria met:
    - tests/BrowserMsalStrategy.test.ts created with 10 test cases (acquireTokenSilent
      happy path, ssoSilent fallback, popup fallback, all-three-fail empty return,
      JWT-exp rejection + fallthrough, no-account path, logout via logoutPopup,
      logout popup-blocked clearCache fallback, clearCache pre-init no-op,
      getMsalInstance pre/post init). Mocks @azure/msal-browser entirely.
    - tests/InMemoryCache.test.ts already had 10 cases from task 012.
    - 39/39 tests pass across the full package suite (was 27/28 — gained 11, lost the
      1 pre-existing config.test.ts baseline which is now fixed).
    - Coverage: BrowserMsalStrategy.ts 80% lines, InMemoryCache.ts 90% lines —
      both meet the >= 80% target. Uncovered lines are Xrm frame-walk paths in
      resolveLoginHint (no Xrm shim in jsdom) and malformed-JWT catch branches.

    BUNDLED CLEANUP (queued by tasks 012-015 as out-of-scope; bundled into 016
    while we're here):
    - Deleted ~50 stale src/**/*.d.ts + src/**/*.js + .map files (pre-v2
      misconfigured build outputs; tsconfig now emits to dist/)
    - Added .gitignore to the package preventing the regression
    - Removed orphaned legacy types (ITokenResult, ITokenStrategy, TokenCacheEntry,
      TokenSource) from types.ts; cleaned up index.ts barrel exports and the
      backward-compat re-export in SpaarkeAuthProvider.ts
    - Fixed tests/config.test.ts to match the v2 contract (no default clientId
      after commit 9e480d75; resolveConfig now throws when clientId is missing)

    COMPREHENSIVE CODE REVIEW (D-AUTH-QUALITY-GATE-DEFERRAL collected) — 10 v2
    source files reviewed. Verdict: APPROVED. 0 critical, 2 warnings (both fixed
    in this same commit), 0 AI code smells, 0 ADR violations. Warnings fixed:
    1. SpaarkeAuthProvider.dispose() now cascades to _cache.clearCache() to prevent
       MSAL-instance leak on initAuth() re-init
    2. BrowserMsalStrategy._validate() bumped near-expiry rejection log from
       console.warn to console.error with msToExpiry + bufferMs payload so the
       upstream-refresh-broken signal surfaces in Application Insights
    Full review report in commit message.

    Phase A COMPLETE. Next: user runs MSAL regression test per
